<plot>After turning 60 years old himself last year, host 'Terry Wogan' (qv) introduces this light-hearted comical look at old age or "geezerdom" as he calls it, a phenomenon that is sweeping the UK. The sketches include news of a new TV station to cater for "old geezers" called UK Old, the launch of a new political party, the Grey Party, and a witty question and answer session in which Terry relates some of the finer, little-known facets of "geezerdom".</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?659585</url></doc>
